						               													<description>What it is: Relatively simple roll-and-move game for children.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Main idea: Crocodile &amp;quot;Kroko&amp;quot; is trying to take a nap at noon but monkey &amp;quot;Jumping Jo&amp;quot; and his friends are robbing him off his sleep by jumping around the pond, trying to reach the trees. This isn't easy, because Kroko can scare them away.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How it is played: Each player gets eight &amp;quot;monkeys&amp;quot; and tries to move them towards the trees. Throwing a 1-4 means moving the same number of spaces. A 5 means you have to move one of your monkeys away from start. If you throw the Kroko side of the die, you give Kroko a push, i.e. you tip the crocodile-shaped spinner in the middle of the board. When Kroko stops, his big tooth points to a specific section of the board. All the monkeys in this area are scared and run back to the start.&amp;#10;Special spaces include Kroko spaces (player has to push Kroko), spaces where a monkey is safe, and liana spaces which allow a monkey to climb to a free space in a tree. The game ends when all tree spaces are occupied. The player who got the highest number of their monkeys to the trees wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
